http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Tap-potential-among-youth%E2%80%99/article13996205.ece

Basava Marulasidda Swami, seer of the Basava Kendra, has stressed the need to channelise the potential among youths towards constructive purposes for the overall development of the nation.He was addressing a National Youth Day programme organised to mark the birth anniversary of Swami Vivekananda at Nehru Indoor Stadium here on Tuesday.The nation, with a vast pool of human resources, lags on several fronts, due to the failure to tap the potential among youth, he said.“Along with providing formal education, it is necessary to plan special programmes to enhance their skills. Training programmes related to personality development should be held in colleges,” he said.He said that Swami Vivekananda strived for the uplift of the poor and downtrodden.Chairperson of Shivamogga Urban Development Authority N. Ramesh inaugurated the programme.